      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>A <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">architrave</rs> block (<measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.42</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="width">2.71</measure> × <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="depth">0.645</measure>) with very simple moulding above two stepped <term>fasciae</term>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> in one line along the upper <term>fascia</term> (H. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.135</measure>).</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>Av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.07</measure>, <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.05</measure>; elongated, irregular; scroll for abbreviation.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date exact="none" cert="low" notBefore="0468" notAfter="0500">Late fifth century</date>.</p>
      </div>

      <div n="text" lang="grc" type="edition">
        <head lang="en">Edition</head>
		<ab><lb n="1"/><g type="cross"/> <persName key="philip1" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Φίλιππος">Φίλιππος</name> <persName key="Herodian" type="aphrodisian" full="yes"><name reg="Ἡροδιανός"><expan><abbr>Ἡροδιαν</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">οῦ</supplied></expan></name></persName></persName> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <rs type="dignity" key="admirandissimus"><w lemma="θαυμάσιος"><expan><abbr>θαυμ</abbr><supplied reason="abbreviation">ασιώτατος</supplied></expan></w></rs> <w lemma="εὐχαριστέω">εὐχαριστῶν</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῇ</w> <w lemma="οἰκία">οἰκίᾳ</w> <w lemma="πατρίς">πατρίδι</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τὰ</w> <num value="2"><hi rend="supraline">β</hi></num> <w lemma="διάχωρον">διάχορα</w> <w lemma="σκεπάζω">ἐσκέπασεν</w> <g type="cross"/></ab>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>Philippos, son of Herodianos, <term lang="la">admirandissimus</term>, returning thanks to his own fatherland, covered <supplied reason="explanation" cert="low">roofed</supplied> the two sections.</ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="V.42">V.42</xref>.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="history" n="locations"><head>Locations</head><p>Found: <rs type="found"><rs type="monuList">South Agora</rs>: South portico, towards west end.</rs>. Original location: <rs type="origLocation">Findspot.</rs>. Last recorded location: <rs type="lastLocation">Findspot.</rs>. </p></div>

      

      

      <div type="history" n="record">
        <head>History of Recording</head>
        <p>Excavated by the NYU expedition in 1971.</p>
      </div>

